      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "That the Schade brewery strike\nis more serious than is indicated\nON lis face, has developed through\nthe arrest on Wednesday Of Frank\nBoofsman, German driver, on a\ncharge of carrying concealed\nweapons. Yesterday he forfeited a\n$40 bond by not appearing in po-\nlice court. Bookman has been a\nunion driver, but did not strike\nwith the others.\n\n\nHe claimed when arrested by\nPatrolman Lawson that he was in\nfear of violence and believed it\nnecessary to go armed in self pro\nlection. Police Chief Rice COM\nmunicated with B. Schade regard\ning the arrest and was informed\nthat Bookman did not go armed\nwith the knowledge of the brewing\ncompany. but that he Is a German\nwho does not know any better and\nhas always been accustomed to\nweapons."
    }
